<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="57" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Russian Ambassador</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington, D. C.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-01"><hi rend="italic">July 1,
                                        1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The Imperial Government, being painfully affected by the news of the
                            sudden death of Secretary of State Hay, instructs me to transmit to the
                            Federal Government the expression of its sincere condolences at this sad
                            event.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cassini.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>